<p><b>Is Hotel California the greatest guitar solo?</b> Wikipedia identifies the solo as voted the best solo of all time by readers of Guitarist magazine in 1998, and was ranked 8th on Guitar Magazine's Top 100 Guitar Solos. So no question its good, really really good and by some standards the best.</p>
<p><b>Who played the 12-string guitar in Hotel California?</b> While the recording features the guitar work of Joe Walsh and Don Felder, the primary guitar heard throughout the solo belongs to Felder, who also wrote the music for the track. In the studio, Felder played the intro on a Takamine 12-string and the solo on his 1959 Les Paul Standard.</p>
